U.S. District Judge Susan Dlott has ordered the IRS to hand over a list of 298 tea party groups that it targeted in 2010 .
The IRS has admitted playing political favorites with the tax code beginning in 2010, when it began applying extra scrutiny to groups with red-flag words like 'patriots' or 'tea party' in their names .
Ruling means right-wing groups can pursue a class-action lawsuit against the IRS .